# <type>(<scope>): <why-it-matters, imperative, <=72 chars>
#
# Allowed types: feat, fix, refactor, perf, test, docs, build, ci, chore, revert
#
# --- Body (delete if commit is truly trivial) -------------------------------
#
# What changed:
#   -
#
# Why:
#   -
#
# Considered & rejected:
#   -
#
# Follow-ups deferred:
#   -
#
# Refs: #<issue or PR>
#
# --- Reminders --------------------------------------------------------------
# - One logical change per commit. Refactor + feature = two commits.
# - Imperative mood. Lowercase after the colon. No trailing period.
# - Subject explains WHY, not just what files changed.
# - Wrap body at ~72 chars.
# - Lines starting with '#' are stripped from the final commit message.
